abstract={Stock verification process in digital libraries having thousands of books, using wired scanners, is time consuming, costly and cumbersome, needing much manual labor and energy. This paper proposes a simple and cost-effective software tool, i.e. a web API based Android application for stock verification process in such libraries by detecting digits in the accession number assigned to each book, journal, periodicals, etc. which can be either machine printed or handwritten irrespective of font type. A Neural Network is designed to model the way in which the brain performs a particular task or function of interest. The neural network is simulated on a digital computer in order to generate a trained model using the standard database of images of handwritten digits. The trained model is used for digit recognition from an image with better accuracy and execution speed. The process of digit recognition is carried out over a cloud platform using Rest API, hence reducing the computational load on handheld devices. This API responds with the detected digits and further logic of verifying the accession number with library's database is carried out on the Android application. Often the cost of carrying out stock verification includes labor, expensive dedicated scanners and time, the proposed system can easily replace the current day stock verification techniques and achieve the same objective with an Android based mobile phone, hence no dependency on the use of dedicated scanners and lesser time constraints.},
